The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, July 9: The CII is preparing a list of suggestions for the government on signing free trade pacts. CII?s WTO and other trade agreement committees will finalise the list soon and will submit it to the government, the chamber said in a release. R.V. Kanoria, chairman of the committee, said the government should consider these inputs while negotiating FTAs. The guidelines will include issues of negative list, common floor tariff and rules of origin, he said.

 New Delhi, July 9: The government is in the process of endowing more power to the directorate-general of hydrocarbons (DGH) to counter gross irregularities in product sharing contracts.

 New Delhi, July 9: Reliance Industries is the only company in the 30-share Bluechip Club to have recovered all the losses incurred during May, which is referred to as the month of mayhem in the recent history of stock market.

 New Delhi, July 9: The Ratan Tata-led Investment Commission has identified South Africa-based Sasol as a potential investor in India for manufacturing alternative fuel.

 Mumbai, July 9: Small Industries Development Bank of India (Sidbi) plans to raise Rs 4,500 crore this fiscal, of which almost Rs 3,000 crore will be raised from overseas financial institutions such as, Asian Development Bank (ADB), World Bank (WB) and KFW of Germany.




